# Documentation sync

When the user makes a decision, or implementation changes facts that are documented elsewhere (test counts, endpoint lists, phase status, verification commands, dates, etc.), **update the appropriate docs in the same change** so the repo stays internally consistent.

Typical targets include:

- `docs/FamLink_Resumption_Prompt.md` — phase status, test counts, “next prompt,” verification notes
- Other `docs/*.md` files when they duplicate or reference those facts

Do not leave stale numbers or contradictions between the codebase and handoff docs when the user has explicitly chosen a new canonical value.
